# Plan Feedback

Before starting implementation from a plan, check if a feedback file exists.

When you are about to build from a plan (e.g. the user says "go", "build it", "start", or "implement the plan"), first check if a file named `<plan-name>-feedback.md` exists in `~/.cursor/plans/` or `.cursor/plans/` in the workspace.

If a feedback file exists:
1. Read it
2. Summarize the feedback to the user
3. Ask if they want to incorporate it before building
4. If yes, update your understanding of the plan accordingly

This ensures team annotations from cursor-plan-preview are applied before implementation begins.
